cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the detection of adversarial examples in deep neural networks. It also involves the training of a separate neural network for this purpose, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper deals with images and their perturbations. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with the security of deep neural networks against adversarial attacks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the behavior of deep neural networks and their susceptibility to adversarial examples. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the detection of adversarial examples in neural networks.
